-- Synergy Rises to Highest in Month on Vodka Sales: Moscow Mover
-- B y   M a r k   S w e e t m a n
-- 2012-01-19T15:25:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/synergy-heads-for-highest-in-month-on-vodka-sales-moscow-mover.html
OAO Synergy (SYNG) , a Russian vodka maker,
rose to its highest close in more than a month and a half after
reporting an 11 percent increase in fourth-quarter sales.  The stock climbed as much as 11 percent to 612.70 rubles in
Moscow before finishing the main trading session at 607.80
rubles, its strongest level since Dec. 5. The 30-stock Micex
Index advanced 0.7 percent to 1,503.70, the fourth consecutive
day of gains.  Synergy, which according to its website employs 7,000
people, increased sales volumes last quarter to 4.89 million
decaliters, while annual output advanced 19 percent to 13.8
million decaliters.  “The company substantially increased its market share and
achieved the leading position on the Russian spirits market,”
Synergy said on its  website  today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Mark Sweetman in Moscow at 
